               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the donor (fol. 91vb); incipits of Text I and its subsections (a few lines are rubricated, alternating with black lines, on fols. 1ra-rb, 10va-vb); incipit of Text II; the word säläm in Text I-1 and from Text I-4 up to Text I-14; the word ʾO-zä-...and the following verbal form in Text I-2; the word tämaḫǝḍänku in Text I-3; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>First six strophes are missing for Text I-14 (fols. 86ra-91va).</note>
                     <note>Possibly, the Vita of ʾabunä Tärbu is a Synaxarion commemorative notice (absent, however, in the edited version of the Ethiopic Synaxarion).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
